    "description": "Join the Sharekhan Global Group family as a Financial Analyst in Aurangabad. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout Sharekhan Global Group:\nSharekhan Global Group is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n• Conduct due diligence for mergers, acquisitions, and investments\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Liaise with banks, regulators, and financial institutions\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Power BI\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in Risk Management\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in GST\n• Proficiency in Forecasting\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Flexible working hours\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Learning & development budget\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Aurangabad, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Sharekhan Global Group!",
